content: This year has been simultaneously one of the best and worst years of my life. I have been given the opportunity of travel & to start a business venture I am passionate about. But I also lost my father after he passed away earlier this year. I decided to take what I have dubbed the _ÜÛLea Michele_Ü_ approach to grief after being inspired by something she said in an interview about her own tragic loss - "at one point that there is an empowerment that comes with grief. At some point you find it. It's very hard, but you will find it._Ü I_Ü_m not going to lie and say there hasn_Ü_t been some hard days and there has certainly been a lot of soul searching. What I have learned is there is always going to be highs and lows in life. It doesn_Ü_t need to be grief necessarily, but sadness, confusion or just road blocks that make you want to give up. Don_Ü_t give up. You never know who is watching how you handle your own trial as the inspiration on how to get through theirs. So don_Ü_t stop, don_Ü_t give in because they may never get to start if you do. You can_Ü_t control what comes to you, but you can control what comes through you. As with anything tough that comes your way - you can choose to fall, or you can choose to rise. All you can do is your best and hopefully make a positive impact through your choices & actions. Whatever it is you're going through, you can get through it. _Žä"
